The SAPS Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit is investigating a case of an abandoned baby.It is believed that the baby could be about two days old.This comes after a passer-by found the child in a box stashed in overgrown bushes, on the corner of Charl Street in Beaconsfield, Kimberley on Sunday.The lady took the baby girl home with her and immediately called the police.The baby is healthy.Members of the public have been urged to call Detective Capt Nadia Kika on 082 469 0697 if they have any information about the baby or the mother of the child.-TNA Reporter